From our live Blue Nile dataset, all G color GIA Excellent Cut 1ct round diamonds:

| Clarity | Price | Stone |
|---------|-------|-------|
| G-VS2 | $3,230 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29090690?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| G-VS2 | $3,240 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29090694?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| G-VS1 | $3,300 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29161966?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| G-VS1 | $3,530 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28823788?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| G-VVS2 | $3,650 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25530212?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| G-VVS2 | $3,760 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29161969?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |

The step from VS2 ($3,230) to VVS2 ($3,650) costs **$420** more for a grade that provides zero additional visible beauty. That $420 could upgrade you half a color grade, or fund a better setting.

At VS2, you already have a stone that is eye-clean in essentially all viewing conditions and under any reasonable examination. The inclusions at VS2 are visible under 10× magnification but require careful searching even then.

