## Real Price Impact at 2 Carats — Where Clarity Savings Scale Up

From our 2ct natural round diamond dataset:

| Clarity | Price | Stone |
|---------|-------|-------|
| G-VS2 | $16,490 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29307739?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| G-VS1 | $22,460 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29249620?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| G-VVS2 | $26,610 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28819967?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| G-IF | $31,380 | [View Stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29286918?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |

At 2 carats, stepping from VS2 ($16,490) to VVS2 ($26,610) costs **$10,120** extra — for a clarity grade the naked eye cannot detect. The G-IF at $31,380 adds another **$14,890** on top of VS2 for a Flawless certificate that makes zero visible difference to anyone looking at the ring.

This is the Clarity Cliff made real: $14,890 to buy a grade that exists only under a loupe.

